|CKBOverdrive|000

|CK0Overdrive is passive burst-control firmware unlocked at Street Samurai
Guild Level 14. It requires the right-ear Overdrive Module and has no
activation command, SP cost, Edge cost, or Heat cost.|000

|CKBOpening burst control|000
|CK0When firmware first tries to add Heat during an engagement, Overdrive can
automatically vent most or all of that opening burst. Once it intervenes, the
profile is spent for the current engagement. Samstatus and the combat monitor
report whether Overdrive is ready or spent.|000

|CK0Overdrive reduces one incoming Heat request. It does not raise maximum
Heat, accelerate normal cooling, remove Heat already present, or prevent all
later lockout risk. If part of the burst remains, Cold Signal can still reduce
that remainder before it reaches the Cortex.|000

|CKBWhat affects it|000
|CK0Hardware grade determines how aggressively the opening profile can vent,
while integrity and fragmentation affect its reliability. The module also
provides passive intelligence and spell-point hardware benefits even after its
Heat profile has been spent.|000

|CKBUsing it well|000
|CK0Overdrive gives an engagement a cleaner opening, so it is most valuable
when the first successful routine would otherwise create substantial Heat.
Watch OD on the monitor or overdrive in samstatus, then plan the rest of the
fight around ordinary Heat, Cold Signal, and available headroom.|000
